snippet.textDisplay:
I don't know why but I feel like he's implying that they are blaming it on this so-called ADHD. But the truth is ADHD in adults tend to be routed from depression. Around our time as kids a lot of us were being 'diagnosed" with ADHD.

I don't know but I feel like there's a deeper message. I don't think he thinks it's his ADHD. I don't think he believes he even has ADHD. It's like he's just trying to find a reason to explain all the pain. And that's just what they told him. And that's all he has so he takes it. IDK I'll shut up. But I was one of those kids. And they forced me to take medication that I did not really need.... I couldn't eat... I always felt like I hadn't slept for days .... And the kids at school would always mention it. . "Oh look Rich is going to get his medicine!" But later in my life I realize, there's a lot to it. I'm clinically depressed, and it was hard for me to keep a job at times.

It was it until recently I found the love of my life. And she's all I need. Love and affection is all you need. Medication will only ruin you further..... Please don't give it to your kids.
